title: For Sale:  Patriot Ordinance Factory P-415 14.5" 5.56
postcontent: This POF P-415 has had *maybe* 200rds through it, but is mostly a "safe queen", so I'd like to sell it to make the wife happy.  I paid full retail in a local gun shop in Texas, but asking resale price of $1800, private sale, no tax.  Everything on the POF is original with the exception of the Magpul ASAP end plate for single-point sling attachment.  The pinned compensator brings overall barrel length to 16", and does a great job of keeping flat follow-up shots for rapid fire.  Ideal optics would be any red dot, or an ACOG, but would do very well scoped for longer range as well.  The barrel is 1/8 twist, fluted with a big heat-dissipating barrel nut, and ready for essentially any application.  The action is piston-driven with a very slick BCG, all very easy to clean.  The piston system has a setting for suppressed, if you're planning to go that route.  Like I said, ready to be customized for essentially any application.

On May 1, 1996, the first HK MK 23 pistols were delivered to the U.S. Special Operations Command for operational deployment, making the MK 23 the first caliber .45 ACP pistol to enter American military service since the venerable Government Model 1911A1.

title: For Sale:  ****SCAM*****
postcontent:
If anyone is contacted by a James Clton, Michael Junior, or anyone texting you first and insisting that you email them back to talk, be wary. This person has contacted me and wanted to use Paypal for the transaction on a rifle. Since he did not live anywhere near me, he stated that he would be sending someone to pick it up. After exchanging Paypal information I was emailed several times (with the exact same email) by someone calling themselves Pedro and stating that they were holding the amount (the term escrow was never used) since it was a large sum of money, and a verification of funds email would soon follow. Even though he started off as Pedro, the email was signed as the President of Paypal. Information anyone with even slight Google-fu can look up.

Not too long after that, I received an email from the person that wanted to purchase the rifle, stating that the party that would be picking up the rifle has to be paid via Western Union before they would come and pick up the rifle. He stated that he included the amount for the Western Union payment along with their fee with the payment for the weapon. Without disclosing dollar amounts, the amount to be paid to the transporter was over 50% of the price for the rifle. As if that wasn't a tip off enough, the large amount, combined with the following email from Paypal definitely was. The next email I received (again received multiple times) stated that Paypal would hold the money until I went and paid the "Company" that would be picking up the rifle (and it was a guy's name, not a company) the $900 and sent Paypal security a copy of the receipt. Only when I had paid the $900 out of pocket would they release the money owed for the rifle, a reimbursement for the $900, and an extra $100 for the Western Union fees.

Not only were the emails in severely broken english, but why in the world would Paypal hold money in escrow until a third party had been paid for services that had not even been rendered yet. Also, why would a person want me to pay someone to pick up a purchase for him instead of paying them himself? A long read, but a cautionary one. Stay away from scams out there guys and gals.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Springfield Armory krag Jorgensen
postcontent:
This is a Springfield Armory Krag Jorgensen chambered in 30-40 Krag. It used to be an 1898 full sized rifle but sometime in its life it was cut down to a 20" barreled carbine. In my opinion it was a rather tasteful sporterization. The receiver is not drilled or tapped and the wood dose not have any cheesy checkering or anything like that. There is no rust or pitting anywhere on this gun. while there is not much bluing left ( I doubt it would be original anyway ) it has a very handsome patina. There are no cracks on the locking lug or bolt shank but there are some small and long hairline cracks on the upper handguard. You can see the most obvious one in the 3rd photo. It has a 2 position mauser style saftey that locks up the action when engaged. The capacity is 5+1, but is also equiped with a magazine cutoff switch for use as a single shot. Standard features for the time. The rear sight, when folded has increments of 100, 200, 300, B (battlefield zero perhaps? ) and 400 yards. If you flip the ladder up the notch resumes at 500 yards and goes up to 1900. With the ladder still up you also get a pep style appeture sight from 100 to 1800 yards. And finally on the very top of the ladder is a knotch set at 2000 yards. 

While this has lost its collectability because of the chopped barrel, it's still a piece of Americana, made by the REAL Springfield arsenal before they sold their name. So in that regard if you want something that still has a bit of history to it, but don't want to feel guilty about shooting, this may be of interest. I will include 40 factory bitterroot valley cartridges as well
Cash price is firm. Trade value 425.00
